    <briefdescription>
<para>This file contains the SLH-DSA address structure (ADRS) and manipulation functions. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The ADRS provides domain separation for hash functions across different SLH-DSA operations including FORS, WOTS+, XMSS, and Hypertree.</para><para><preformatted>
MODIFICATION HISTORY:</preformatted></para><para><preformatted>Ver   Who  Date     Changes
----- ---- -------- ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5.7   tvp  02/19/26 Initial release</preformatted></para><para><preformatted></preformatted></para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para>All multi-byte values are stored in big-endian order within the ADRS structure. </para></simplesect>
</para>    </detaileddescription>
